# The MCP server's env now lives in the repo root .env (one file for the whole
# project). See ../.env.example for FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID,
# GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS, and FLOWMANCER_API_KEY.
#
# The npm scripts here read it via `--env-file=../.env`, and agent-hook.js loads
# it from the repo root. Use an ABSOLUTE GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS path so
# it resolves the same regardless of which directory the command runs from.
